<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910412-0034</DOCNO><DOCID>910412-0034.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- A.O. Smith Corp.:   Large First-Quarter Deficit   Posted on Declining Sales</HL><DATE>04/12/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   SMCA SMCB</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>AUTO PARTS AND EQUIPMENT INCLUDING TIRES (AUP)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>WISCONSIN (WI)</RE><LP>   A.O. Smith Corp., hurt by the auto industry's slump,reported a big first-quarter loss on declining sales.   The Milwaukee-based manufacturer said it had a loss of$857,000, or 22 cents a share, in the latest period, a sharpreversal from year-ago earnings of $4.9 million, or 51 centsa share. Sales fell 16%, to $200 million from $237.2 million.</LP><TEXT>   The auto sector's slowdown &quot;significantly affected&quot;first-quarter performance at Smith's automotive productsdivision, which makes structural components, primarily forlight trucks.   The &quot;magnitude of Automotive's loss overshadowed&quot; whatSmith called encouraging performance at its other majoroperating companies, including its glass fiber products unit,and its water-heater manufacturing unit.</TEXT></DOC>